  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "In a medium bowl, mix together the crumbled feta cheese, labneh cheese, chopped cilantro, scallions, parsley, dill, garlic, and walnuts.",
    "In a small bowl, whisk together the lemon juice and olive oil.",
    "Pour the lemon juice mixture over the cheese mixture and stir until well combined.",
    "Season with salt to taste.",
    "Cover the bowl with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes to allow the flavors to meld.",
    "While the cheese mixture is chilling, cook the warak-enab dumplings according to the package instructions.",
    "Once the dumplings are cooked, place them on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.",
    "Drizzle the dumplings with a little bit of olive oil and sprinkle with salt.",
    "Bake the dumplings in the preheated oven for 10-12 minutes, or until crispy and golden brown.",
    "To assemble the warak enab, place a few dumplings on a plate, followed by a spoonful of the cheese mixture.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!"
  ],
